## J. DynDNS deSEC — service runit polling 600s sur voidhv

Le script de mise à jour tourne sur **voidhv** (machine la plus stable, toujours allumée). On vise un cycle de **10 min**, largement sous la limite de 300 modifications/jour/domaine de deSEC.

Variables :

```sh
FQDN=farmos.dedyn.io
```

Stocker le token :

```sh
sudo mkdir -p /etc/desec && sudo chmod 700 /etc/desec
echo -n "$DYN_TOKEN" | sudo install -m 0600 /dev/stdin /etc/desec/dyndns.token
```

Script :

```sh
sudo install -m 0755 /dev/stdin /usr/local/bin/desec-update.sh <<'EOF'
#!/bin/sh
# /usr/local/bin/desec-update.sh
set -eu

FQDN=farmos.dedyn.io
TOKEN=$(cat /etc/desec/dyndns.token)

V4=$(curl -fsS --max-time 10 https://checkipv4.dedyn.io || true)
V6=$(curl -fsS --max-time 10 https://checkipv6.dedyn.io || true)

ARGS="hostname=${FQDN}"
if [ -n "${V4:-}" ]; then ARGS="${ARGS}&myipv4=${V4}"; else ARGS="${ARGS}&myipv4=preserve"; fi
if [ -n "${V6:-}" ]; then ARGS="${ARGS}&myipv6=${V6}"; else ARGS="${ARGS}&myipv6=preserve"; fi

logger -t desec-update "PUT ${FQDN} v4=${V4:-?} v6=${V6:-?}"
curl -fsS "https://update.dedyn.io/?${ARGS}" \
  -H "Authorization: Token ${TOKEN}" \
  -o /tmp/desec-update.last
EOF
```

Service runit polling 600s :

```sh
sudo mkdir -p /etc/sv/desec-update/log

sudo install -m 0755 /dev/stdin /etc/sv/desec-update/run <<'EOF'
#!/bin/sh
exec 2>&1
while :; do
    /usr/local/bin/desec-update.sh || echo "[desec-update] curl failed"
    sleep 600
done
EOF

sudo install -m 0755 /dev/stdin /etc/sv/desec-update/log/run <<'EOF'
#!/bin/sh
exec chpst -u _socklog svlogd -tt /var/log/desec-update
EOF

sudo mkdir -p /var/log/desec-update
sudo chown _socklog:_socklog /var/log/desec-update
sudo ln -s /etc/sv/desec-update /var/service/
sleep 12
sudo sv status desec-update
```

**Vérifier :**

```sh
dig +short A   farmos.dedyn.io
dig +short AAAA farmos.dedyn.io
# Doit retourner l'IPv4 publique de la Livebox (ou IPv6 si dispo)
```

⚠️ **Pare-feu sortant** : si tu actives un kill-switch sortant strict sur `voidhv` plus tard, autoriser explicitement `update.dedyn.io` et `checkipv4.dedyn.io` en TCP/443.

